article.headline: Pennsylvania 67, Princeton 52
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Jeff Schiffner scored 22 points and Pennsylvania continued its recent dominance of Ivy League rival Princeton with a 67-52 win Tuesday night. Princeton lost its first Ivy League game to fall to 4-1 in the league, 11-7 overall and is now a half-game behind Cornell (5-1). Penn (10-8, 3-2) won its third straight conference game after opening with two losses for the first time since 1992. In a rivalry that dates back to 1903 and that perennially decides the Ivy League champion -- Penn and Princeton have won or shared 33 of the last 35 conference titles -- Penn has won eight of the last 11 games between the two by an average of 16 points. Will Venable led Princeton with 12 points. Princeton, which averages 13 turnovers per game, committed 10 in the first half and looked discombobulated on offense despite shooting 50 percent (10-of-20) from the field. On the defensive end, the Tigers were unable to stop Penn's inside-outside attack of Mark Zoller, who finished with 16 points, and Schiffner. The freshman and senior combined to outscore Princeton 26-24 in the first 20 minutes. Penn shot a sizzling 15-for-24 (63 percent) from the field in the first half, including 5-of-7 from 3-point range. The Quakers finished 25-of-49 and made nine of 15 3-pointers in the game. Schiffner, the leading 3-point shooter in NCAA Division I last season, made all three of his shots from behind the arc in the first half and helped keep Princeton at bay. After the Tigers closed to 14-12 on a 3-pointer by Ed Persia, Schiffner sank two foul shots and, after a follow shot by Harrison Schaen, made a 3-pointer that started a 9-0 run that included 3-pointers by Tim Begley and Eric Osmundson. Princeton got within seven points at 25-18 on a hook shot by Judson Wallace with 5:27 left, but the Tigers couldn't inch closer as Schiffner made another 3-pointer and Zoller scored 6 points, the final two on a 10-foot baseline jumper with :05 left in the half to give Penn its biggest lead of the half at 38-24. Zoller picked up where he left off in the beginning of the second half with a jumper, drive and a feed to Adam Chubb for a dunk in the first 2:30 that gave Penn a 44-24 lead. Princeton slowly cut into the lead and trailed by 14 on a 3-pointer by Venable with 9:06 left, but Schiffner capped an 8-0 run with another long 3-pointer to push the lead back to 22 with 5:38 left.
